main event: On October 7, 1966, a civilian reported an unidentified object in the sky for approximately 20 minutes.
interesting points: The object was described as oval, three times the size of the full moon, and pulsating with multi-colored lights at the bottom,The observer initially saw a streak of light going up rapidly in the southwest sky,The sighting occurred at 0830Z during the night in clear weather conditions,The observer went to fetch a witness, and upon returning, the object was no longer visible,No physical evidence was found to evaluate the sighting.
sighted object: one oval object pulsating with lights
